        <h2>Senior Introductions That Shine</h2>
        <p>The key to memorable senior introductions is personalization. For each senior, prepare a short anecdote about their time in the program. Mention a specific moment from their career. Ask assistant coaches or teammates for input. The more specific, the more meaningful.</p>

        <h2>Senior Night Decorations & Keepsakes</h2>
        <p>Every senior should walk away with something tangible. Many programs give a small gift or keepsake — a senior night T-shirt, a commemorative photo, or a custom centerpiece for their family table. Decorations set the emotional tone: team-color tablecloths, senior banners with names and numbers, and a photo timeline of the season.</p>

